<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>Recovery Snapshot — {{ case_id }}</title>
{% include "_styles.html.j2" %}
<style>
  /* Recovery Snapshot — pre-engagement deliverable. Designed to be
     shareable with the victim BEFORE they pay the engagement fee.
     The audience is non-technical (the victim's lawyer, possibly the
     victim themselves), so the headline shape is "here's what we
     think you'll get back" — not a forensic worksheet. */
  .snapshot-headline {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #fafafa 0%, #f3f4f6 100%);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--gold-accent);
    padding: 28px 32px;
    margin: 24px 0 32px;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }
  .snapshot-headline-label {
    font-size: var(--type-tiny);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.10em;
    color: var(--ink-quiet);
    margin: 0 0 8px;
  }
  .snapshot-headline-amount {
    font-size: 32px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.0;
  }
  .snapshot-headline-range {
    font-size: var(--type-small);
    color: var(--ink-quiet);
    margin: 8px 0 0;
  }
  .snapshot-recommendation {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 4px 12px;
    border-radius: 12px;
    font-size: var(--type-tiny);
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }
  .snapshot-recommendation.recommend  { background: #DCFCE7; color: #14532D; }
  .snapshot-recommendation.caveat     { background: #FEF3C7; color: #5C2D0F; }
  .snapshot-recommendation.discourage { background: #FED7AA; color: #5C1F09; }
  .snapshot-recommendation.reject     { background: #FECACA; color: #7F1D1D; }
  .driver-pill {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 2px 8px;
    border-radius: 10px;
    font-size: var(--type-tiny);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .driver-pill.positive { background: #DCFCE7; color: #166534; }
  .driver-pill.negative { background: #FECACA; color: #991B1B; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<section class="cover">
  <div class="cover-letterhead">
    <div class="cover-wordmark">
      Recupero
      <span class="tagline">Investigation Services</span>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-letterhead-right">
      <div class="confidential">Pre-engagement Snapshot</div>
      <div class="date">{{ generated_at }} UTC</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="cover-title-block">
    <div class="cover-eyebrow">Case {{ case_id }}</div>
    <h1>Recovery<br/>Snapshot</h1>
    <p class="cover-subtitle">
      An initial assessment of what's recoverable from the trace
      Recupero has completed on your case. The numbers below are
      probability-weighted estimates derived from the per-issuer
      freeze-outcome history we maintain across all prior cases;
      they are not guarantees. The figures will sharpen as freeze
      requests go out and responses land.
    </p>
    <div class="cover-rule"></div>
  </div>
</section>

{# Recommendation pill — the lawyer's TL;DR. #}
<div style="margin: 24px 0 8px;">
  {% set rec = recovery_estimate.get('recommendation') or 'caveat' %}
  <span class="snapshot-recommendation {{ rec }}">
    {% if rec == 'recommend' %}
    Recommended for engagement
    {% elif rec == 'caveat' %}
    Engage with caveat
    {% elif rec == 'discourage' %}
    Engagement discouraged
    {% else %}
    Recovery not advised
    {% endif %}
  </span>
</div>

{# Headline: estimated net to victim. #}
<div class="snapshot-headline">
  <p class="snapshot-headline-label">Projected net recovery to victim</p>
  <p class="snapshot-headline-amount">
    {{ recovery_estimate.get('expected_net_to_victim_usd') or '$0' }}
  </p>
  <p class="snapshot-headline-range">
    95% confidence range:
    {{ recovery_estimate.get('expected_net_low_usd') or '—' }}
    –
    {{ recovery_estimate.get('expected_net_high_usd') or '—' }}
    &nbsp;·&nbsp;
    {% if recovery_estimate.get('probability_any_recovery_90d') %}
    {{ "%.0f%%"|format(recovery_estimate.get('probability_any_recovery_90d') * 100) }} probability of any recovery within 90 days
    {% endif %}
  </p>
</div>

<p>{{ recovery_estimate.get('headline_summary') or '' }}</p>

<h2>1. Per-issuer breakdown</h2>
{% if recovery_estimate.get('per_issuer') %}
<p class="small">
  Each issuer in your case has a different cooperation history and
  different freeze authority. The expected-recovery column accounts
  for both factors plus the strength of the underlying evidence
  (confirmed current balance versus historical receipt).
</p>
<table class="evidence">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Issuer</th>
      <th>Frozen if successful</th>
      <th>Probability we succeed</th>
      <th>Expected recovery</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    {% for row in recovery_estimate.get('per_issuer') %}
    <tr>
      <td><strong>{{ row.issuer }}</strong></td>
      <td class="amount">{{ row.requested_usd_human }}</td>
      <td>
        <strong>{{ row.effective_prior_pct }}</strong>
        {% if row.is_learned_prior %}
        <br/><span class="small secondary">(from {{ row.issuer }}'s prior responses)</span>
        {% else %}
        <br/><span class="small secondary">(industry heuristic)</span>
        {% endif %}
      </td>
      <td class="amount"><strong>{{ row.expected_recovered_usd_human }}</strong></td>
    </tr>
    {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>
{% else %}
<p class="small">No freezable issuer holdings identified in this case.</p>
{% endif %}

<h2>2. What's helping and what's hurting</h2>
{% if recovery_estimate.get('drivers') %}
<p class="small">
  Recovery probability is not just about which issuers hold the
  funds — it's also about the jurisdiction of every party in the
  chain, whether the funds passed through any sanctioned
  infrastructure, and how concentrated the recoverable amount is.
  The drivers below explain the headline number.
</p>
<ul>
  {% for d in recovery_estimate.get('drivers') %}
  <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">
    <span class="driver-pill {{ d.direction }}">
      {% if d.direction == 'positive' %}+{% else %}−{% endif %}
      {{ d.factor }}
    </span>
    &nbsp;{{ d.description }}
  </li>
  {% endfor %}
</ul>
{% endif %}

<h2>3. What happens next</h2>
<p>
  If you elect to proceed with the engagement:
</p>
<ol>
  <li>
    Recupero will transmit formal freeze requests to every issuer
    listed above within 24 hours. The freeze window for stablecoin
    issuers is typically 72 hours — moving fast materially improves
    the odds of an intact freeze.
  </li>
  <li>
    A monitoring subscription will be activated on every wallet in
    your case. If funds move at any time during the engagement, you
    will receive an email within minutes and your case dashboard will
    reflect the new state in real time.
  </li>
  <li>
    Within seven days, you will have a status update with the
    formal acknowledgements from each issuer. The recovery number
    above will be revised based on what each issuer actually
    confirms.
  </li>
  <li>
    If any issuer goes silent past the standard escalation window
    (typically 14 days), Recupero will recommend a pivot to a formal
    legal instrument (grand jury subpoena, MLAT request, or FinCEN
    314(b) information-sharing request) — and prepare the relevant
    documents on your behalf.
  </li>
</ol>

<h2>4. What this snapshot is not</h2>
<p class="small">
  <strong>Not a guarantee.</strong> The expected recovery figure is
  a probability-weighted estimate, not a contractual promise. Real
  outcomes depend on factors outside Recupero's control — issuer
  responsiveness on any given day, jurisdictional cooperation, and
  the perpetrator's actions during the freeze window.
</p>
<p class="small">
  <strong>Not legal advice.</strong> Recovery of stolen
  cryptocurrency frequently requires a licensed attorney to file
  the formal legal instruments. Recupero prepares the supporting
  forensic evidence and draft documents but does not represent
  victims in legal proceedings.
</p>
<p class="small">
  <strong>Not the full case record.</strong> The complete forensic
  trace, freeze requests, and law-enforcement handoff documents
  remain separate deliverables generated alongside this snapshot.
  This document is a one-page summary intended for the engagement
  decision.
</p>

<footer class="brief-footer">
  <div class="footer-brand">Recupero · Investigation Services</div>
  <div class="footer-meta">
    <code>{{ case_id }}</code><br/>
    Generated {{ generated_at }} UTC · v{{ software_version }}<br/>
    <span class="confidential">Pre-engagement Snapshot.</span>
    Shareable with the victim, the victim's counsel, and the
    insurer; not for distribution to issuer compliance teams or
    law enforcement — those audiences are served by the full
    freeze-request and LE-handoff deliverables.
  </div>
</footer>

</body>
</html>
